Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost Conan's tenth anniversary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.24,0:00:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Overcoming one obstacle, and aiming for the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.13,0:00:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a prank by the God of meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.60,0:00:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Patterned after the legend of the Eight-Headed Serpent...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan tackles the mystery of this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.01,0:00:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.52,0:00:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.27,0:00:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.07,0:01:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.90,0:01:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll do a little sightseeing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.86,0:02:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then eat and drink a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.08,0:02:06.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You sure are acting differently\Nthan you were on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:08.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Scary, scary scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.25,0:02:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place we traveled to this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:16.25,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Izumo Grand Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.79,0:02:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the old, mythical village of...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sword of the Eight-Headed Serpent:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.96,0:02:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.35,0:02:27.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We came all the way to the Grand\NShrine of Izumo, the God of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.43,0:02:30.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I understand why Ran absolutely had to see it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.73,0:02:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please find me a good match.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.07,0:02:36.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Jeez, what kind of lover's hopes are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's do this here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.70,0:02:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, quite an impressive number here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.00,0:02:46.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: The "knot of love" or "en-musubi" is a Japanese amulet which is said to\Nbring love and marriage to its owner when tied to the tree Izumo blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.61,0:02:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then... Tie the knot of love, tie the knot of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:51.80,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: A Shimenawa is a braided rice straw rope\Nused for ritual purification in the Shinto religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.75,0:02:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the biggest Shimenawa in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It really is huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.71,0:02:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Absolutely unbeatable...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It weighs five tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.05,0:02:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, five tons?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.26,0:03:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.35,0:03:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it look even better than on television?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.81,0:03:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better to see it in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um... Are you working here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm Ezumi Eiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.32,0:03:18.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,0)} Ezumi Eiko (25\N{\fs13}Sunrise Shop - Eldest Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.67,0:03:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I work at a small shop in front of the path to this shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a small shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.78,0:03:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! I'm his daughter, Ran, and this is Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.03,0:03:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.37,0:03:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.62,0:03:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that money up there for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.16,0:03:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right! There are a lot of coins stuck to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a legend that says...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your coin gets stuck there, your wish will come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means it can also bless my wish for a good match.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.06,0:03:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:03:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.98,0:04:01.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It looks like your wish will never come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.82,0:04:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You live in a town that's so well-known for marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but I just wish I could get a real marriage proposal...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.79,0:04:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A "real" one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean someone already popped the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it! The guy who proposed must be too poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has quite a bit of money,\Nsince he deals with a lot of businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.88,0:04:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, does he have a bad personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.97,0:04:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rich person with a bad personality,\Nthat's the absolute worst combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.89,0:04:34.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Getting married to him is a tragedy waiting to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the circumstances won't allow me to decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.82,0:04:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Marriage is about bonding\Nwith the person one really loves...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.99,0:04:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what's this guy's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.49,0:04:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Wanibuchi Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You told us that there are some circumstances,\Nbut marrying Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} when you don't love him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.75,0:04:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that like throwing your life away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.75,0:04:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.50,0:05:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, please excuse him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was just telling me that for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.05,0:05:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.47,0:05:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to go see an interesting model?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.26,0:05:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An interesting model?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumo Grand Shrine originally looked like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:17.58,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Ancient Izumo Grand Shrine- Museum Model Exhibition
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.35,0:05:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It certainly was hard to get to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.28,0:05:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've been one of the world's wonders!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.11,0:05:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was said to be the biggest temple in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're interested in hearing more...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:29.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: The Heian period was from 794- 1185,\Nand the Kamakura period was from from 1185- 1333.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We believe this piece of art dates back to the late\NHeian period or the beginning of the Kamakura period...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's Fukuma Ryousuke, a childhood friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.12,0:05:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been interested in the ancient\Ntimes ever since he was a young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:43.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Fukuma Ryousuke (25)\N{\fs16} Museum Curator
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:43.39,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Researching about them made him so happy,\Nhe decided to make a living doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.34,0:05:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s true feelings for Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.14,0:05:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's definitely in love with Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.77,0:05:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this guy is the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.06,0:06:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you realized that a rich guy with a\Nbad personality can't snatch Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} away?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.81,0:06:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.74,0:06:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.24,0:06:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.45,0:06:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for today, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.12,0:06:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem. Best of luck to\Nyou in getting out of that proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.25,0:06:25.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're talking so seriously again,\Nbut what are you really thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.72,0:06:28.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then, the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.47,0:06:29.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A case occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worth 10 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:47.09,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,0)}Inome Cave
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was stabbed in the back with a knife, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.91,0:06:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outsiders aren't allowed to come in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.04,0:06:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.79,0:06:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a private detective from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so. I often hear about your great work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Yamane from the Izumo Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm Komura, from the same prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.38,0:07:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Formalities aside, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.22,0:07:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't seem like this case will\Nrequire the abilities of a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is from Izumo,\Na man renowned for his business skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.65,0:07:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Founder and president of Wanibuchi Enterprises...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.77,0:07:27.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanibuchi Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 35 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.07,0:07:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanibuchi Kouji?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.95,0:07:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us she was engaged to!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.70,0:07:35.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That guy sure was killed at a convenient time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.24,0:07:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was famous in this area for\Nbeing a powerful businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.71,0:07:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first to discover the body was this couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.17,0:07:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're also locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this isn't really a place where tourists would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.59,0:07:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We estimate the time of death to be around 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.68,0:07:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume that Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nwatch broke when he fell over...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.31,0:07:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died when the watch hands stopped at 1:05 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.72,0:08:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that certainly confirms the time of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think the murderer was\Nsomeone who held a grudge against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.77,0:08:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he was a powerful businessman with a\Nbad attitude, he must have made a lot of enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true that he didn't have the best reputation...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.16,0:08:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's goal was to steal a katana,\Nwhich was valued at 10 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A katana worth 10 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.21,0:08:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s property.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He went to an antique shop in the city this afternoon, and\Nreceived the katana as a repayment of the owner's debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.14,0:08:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went to that shop earlier, and he\Nconfirmed that he gave it to Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} around noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.18,0:08:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he received the katana, he walked\Nacross the bridge and came here, to the Inome Cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.77,0:08:52.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know why he came here, but he was witnessed\Ncarrying the katana on this bridge shortly before 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when the corpse was discovered,\Nthe katana was nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.16,0:09:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we can guess that the culprit saw\NWanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} get the katana at the antique shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.46,0:09:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And followed him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this murder was carried\Nout simply to steal the priceless treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.84,0:09:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, there's no need for a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.89,0:09:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see where you're coming from now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.77,0:09:23.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.39,0:09:27.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this a really such an open and shut case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.02,0:09:29.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would the culprit have\Nwaited until he got to this specific place?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.15,0:09:32.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Moreover, walking around with\Na katana worth 10 million yen...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:35.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you snooping around for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't doing anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel bad that we can't do\Nanything about Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.24,0:09:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it good that Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwon't have to marry him anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.46,0:09:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, I shouldn't have put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.67,0:09:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you also say something like that yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.17,0:09:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you always say "If you're forced into\Nmarriage, it's like throwing your life away?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:10:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this murder remind you of\N"The Extermination of the Eight-Headed Serpent"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Extermination of the Eight-Headed Serpent"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a legend about Susanoo's admirable act.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.39,0:10:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There once was a pitiable princess who had been\Ntaken by the Eight-Headed Serpent against her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the admirable Susanoo appeared and\Nkilled the Eight-Headed Serpent, saving the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.95,0:10:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This case reminded me of this story\Nbecause he also obtained the serpent's sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.79,0:10:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't they similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.75,0:10:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Susanoo's act may have been heroic...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But our case's culprit isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.92,0:10:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have coincidentally saved\NEiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from being stuck in a doomed marriage...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he's no more than a robber and a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.97,0:10:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just saying this is almost like\Nthe extermination of that serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.18,0:10:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:49.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But, just as I suspected...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.69,0:10:52.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This case wasn't a simple robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.25,0:11:03.39,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Inasa Beach
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.52,0:11:03.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Once a year, all the gods in Japan gather\Ntogether in Izumo to discuss Everyone's issues..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Here on Isana beach."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.33,0:11:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They weren't even listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you pay attention when I'm saying something to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.21,0:11:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.43,0:11:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.22,0:11:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just got confirmation from one\Nof the antique shop's employees...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.81,0:11:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that this is the same katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.10,0:11:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did they take the time to steal the\Nkatana, only to hide it in the sand later on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't hide it, they threw it\Naway because it was worthless for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They took it from the crime scene as camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.58,0:11:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wanted to lead us to believe that their goal was theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.45,0:11:50.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the most likely scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.25,0:11:52.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And that means that the culprit's true intention was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:54.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To kill Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing that their motive was\Nthat they held a grudge against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.30,0:12:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get me a list of those people!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.47,0:12:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Include his business rivals, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.38,0:12:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also include anyone who has\Nhad any problems with Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.35,0:12:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.47,0:12:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... Uh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.32,0:12:17.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,0)}Shimane Prefecture: Izumo Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:16.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The list was completed the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.48,0:12:19.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}And four people were called to the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:25.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two of those people were... Eiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.41,0:12:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we're ready to begin the questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.12,0:12:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before that, I'd like to introduce you to\Nsomeone who will be helping us in our investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The detective, Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:52.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No, it's just that I never imagined I'd get\Nto see such a famous detective in Izumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.48,0:12:52.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Fujie Takehiko (40)\N{\fs10} Manager of a Marriage Ceremony Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, Ishitobi Kazuya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.31,0:12:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.73,0:12:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to this information...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:04.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Ishitobi Kazuya (35)\N{\fs10} Manager of the Izumo Soba Restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:03.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} offered you a joint management deal...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To help revive your dying Izumo Soba restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.41,0:13:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What "joint management?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:14.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wanibuchi Enterprises will take\Ncare of all the restaurant's capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.58,0:13:18.67,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But in return, I'll get the rights to use the Ishitobi name\Nand to mass-market your soba throughout Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:20.42,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Quite a delicious proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:22.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.84,0:13:25.34,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're not in a position to decline the offer, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.68,0:13:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy was using financial threats to take over the\Nrestaurant that's been in my family for over 200 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.77,0:13:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.18,0:13:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moving on, the next suspect is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.43,0:13:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujie Takehiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who manages the\NRyouunkaku Marriage Ceremony Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.69,0:13:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm in the same situation as Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.11,0:13:47.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wanibuchi Enterprises was planning\Non opening a marriage ceremony hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.95,0:13:53.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But it would be hard to draw customers away from\Nan old, well-known establishment like Ryouunkaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:55.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's why I want to make a deal with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.50,0:14:01.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll teach you our methods,\Nthen we'll both manage this place my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:02.21,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.22,0:14:07.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Fujie{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-senpai{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.60,0:14:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did he address you as "Senpai?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.51,0:14:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanibuchi was my kouhai at the\NTeito University of Business in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.81,0:14:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, university?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.02,0:14:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crocodile Snake\NHis name is "Wani", but he seems more like a "hebi".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.23,0:14:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a monster that's always meddling in other\Npeople's business and appropriating whatever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.46,0:14:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, he's just like an evil serpent!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.95,0:14:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.33,0:14:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iezumi Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you also met\NWanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for your first time at work, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.08,0:14:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, my family and I own the old Hinode Inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.04,0:14:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while the building was deteriorating a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.17,0:14:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't in need of repairs yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.42,0:14:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, a Tokyo-based firm\Nwanted to remodel it into a modern hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they came and talked to us about selling it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just when my parents started to lose hope\Nbecause they might need to part with their inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:01.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10} I can't believe that you would let a\Nhistorical site like Hinode Inn be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.65,0:15:05.15,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please let me help you with the reconstruction fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.57,0:15:07.03,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}For all of Izumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was surprising...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.28,0:15:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we heard he was\Nsomeone that acted only on his self interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.49,0:15:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So my parents accepted his offer and renovated the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:20.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You want to marry my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.12,0:15:22.50,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are you saying all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.88,0:15:25.21,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's not sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:29.47,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she becomes my wife, I'll be compensated\Nfor all the money I lent you for this renovation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.47,0:15:31.13,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.76,0:15:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had this planned from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.93,0:15:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I declined his marriage proposal,\Nwe would have to repay all the money he lent us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.35,0:15:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.14,0:15:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My parents didn't want me to marry that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.02,0:15:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they? told me they'd abandon their inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.78,0:15:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I knew how precious this inn was to my parents,\Nsince it had been passed down for generations, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.87,0:15:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you couldn't leave Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} alone in that situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You begged Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ndozens of times to withdraw that deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.54,0:16:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did. I also hated that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, let's discuss the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.77,0:16:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me where you were and\Nwhat you were doing yesterday at 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.15,0:16:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's start with...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at Matsue Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.27,0:16:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Matsue Castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.45,0:16:32.88,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}Matsue Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went by myself, so I have no witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:40.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: The register states that Fujie Takehiko came to the castle at 1:05 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! But I signed on the castle's entrance register!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.41,0:16:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.58,0:16:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the day off yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.37,0:16:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I went to the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was there from a little before noon to 3:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:53.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Former Grand Shrine Station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.17,0:16:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I often go there to unwind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.72,0:16:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since I went there alone, no one can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:16:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Ishitobi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.26,0:17:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I was at the Izumo Traditional Cultural Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.75,0:17:06.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)}Izumo Traditional Cultural Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... I was also alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.44,0:17:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally... Ezumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.86,0:17:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to Hinomisaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also went alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.50,0:17:18.26,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Hinomisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.53,0:17:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had heard that seagull season arrived earlier than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.49,0:17:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't see any there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Komura, go and confirm their testimonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.08,0:17:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.67,0:17:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone went to famous tourist spots...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So wouldn't a lot of people have seen them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.84,0:17:35.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they really did what they said, then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:37.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.26,0:17:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.56,0:17:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got confirmation for Fujie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's his handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.73,0:17:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And based on the times of those before and after him,\Nit's also true that he was at Matsue Castle at 1:05 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:55.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}1:05 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:18:00.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He signed the register at the exact same time as the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Travelling from Matsue Castle to the crime scene in Inome...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would take between 40 minutes to an hour by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.71,0:18:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.33,0:18:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I shouldn't be under suspicion anymore, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.96,0:18:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem lies with the three others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.88,0:18:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that none of them had a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.05,0:18:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.35,0:18:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even one between the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.01,0:18:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As we couldn't confirm your alibis, we\Ncan't remove you from the suspects list.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.19,0:18:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I'm going to have you re-testify, but this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a private, one-on-one discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.91,0:18:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} aren't the culprits right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.16,0:18:47.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But no matter how we look at it, no one had a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:49.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That means someone is probably lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.71,0:18:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Yamane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.92,0:18:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.55,0:19:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.93,0:19:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go and catch him before he leaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.93,0:19:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukuma Ryousuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.35,0:19:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.68,0:19:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found a witness who states he saw someone burying\NSomething at Inasa Beach around 2:00 PM yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.44,0:19:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They described the man as a "tall, slender individual?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had forensics analyze your shoes, and found traces of\Nsand from Inasa Beach and soil from Inome Cave on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want to confess... to killing Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.38,0:19:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's keeping silent?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.75,0:19:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but if we assume he's the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.55,0:19:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can build some theories, even though there\Nweren't any witnesses at the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.59,0:19:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he murdered Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in Inome,\Nhe must have gone to Inasa Beach to dispose of the katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.81,0:19:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that settles it. It had to have been Fukuma Ryousuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true that there's a witness\Nand that forensics found sand on his shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.44,0:20:02.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That only proves he removed the katana\Nfrom the crime scene and buried it at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.53,0:20:04.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.33,0:20:08.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It doesn't prove that he's the murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.37,0:20:12.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I went to Hinomisaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:16.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That reaction... Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.00,0:20:18.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He knew where Eiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} really went!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:20.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.47,0:20:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.10,0:20:25.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,Interrogation Room 1
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.27,0:20:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.60,0:20:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Walking into the interrogation room without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.89,0:20:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't do that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.48,0:20:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} won't talk,\NI thought he was covering up for the real culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:44.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.74,0:20:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Told you so!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.33,0:20:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have seen something at the Inome cave...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the real culprit attacked Wanibuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.75,0:20:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who could the real culprit be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.58,0:20:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person he would cover up for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.01,0:21:04.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You witnessed Ezumi Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.01,0:21:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you took the katana to\Nmake it look like a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.85,0:21:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.60,0:21:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who killed Wanibuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.60,0:21:15.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Say whatever you want, but it's already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.94,0:21:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me? I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.82,0:21:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where did you actually\Ngo during the time of the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you went to Hinomisaki,\Nbut no one saw you there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.99,0:21:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither the lighthouse nor the souvenir shop employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.37,0:21:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.87,0:21:36.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This woman's doing the same thing as Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.33,0:21:38.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She's covering up for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.84,0:21:41.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I had the day of yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.91,0:21:43.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So I went to the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.28,0:21:45.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.26,0:21:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.97,0:21:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know that Fukuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the culprit,\Nso you're covering up for him, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.45,0:21:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.06,0:22:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, come with me for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.34,0:22:06.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.21,0:22:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are both protecting their lover...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.27,0:22:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who is the real culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.73,0:22:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that neither of them are the true culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.52,0:22:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I wanna check.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.99,0:22:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.35,0:22:28.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To the former Grand Shrine station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:24:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, all of the suspects are innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.39,0:24:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.40,0:24:04.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.56,0:24:07.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's an extra row that's not on yesterday's page.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.94,0:24:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.03,0:24:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mutual misunderstanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.20,0:24:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Mouri. I need to meet with you as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.57,0:24:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll let you know why when you get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.62,0:24:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: Sword of the Eight-Headed Serpent, Part 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.88,0:24:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.17,0:24:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A false testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.28,0:24:31.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You tied your knot of love\Nthinking of Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.98,0:24:32.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.74,0:24:33.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,T-Then, who?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.25,0:24:34.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,W-W-Who?!
